import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.scatter(data['x'], data['y'])
    ax.set_xlabel('x')
    ax.set_ylabel('y')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between x and y?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.hist(data['x'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    ax.axvline(data['x'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['x'].mean():.2f}")
    ax.axvline(data['x'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['x'].median():.2f}")
    ax.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.hist(data['y'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    ax.axvline(data['y'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f'median={data["y"].median():.2f}')
    ax.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of y?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.boxplot([data['x'], data['y']])
    ax.set_xticklabels(['x', 'y'])
    plt.title('What is the range of x and y values?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['quadrant'] = pd.cut(data['x'], bins=[-1, 0, 1], labels=['left', 'right'])
    data['quadrant'] = data['quadrant'].astype(str) + pd.cut(data['y'], bins=[-1, 0, 1], labels=['bottom', 'top']).astype(str)
    data['quadrant'] = pd.Categorical(data['quadrant'], categories=['leftbottom', 'lefttop', 'rightbottom', 'righttop'], ordered=True)
    data = data.sort_values('quadrant')
    colors = {'leftbottom': 'red', 'lefttop': 'blue', 'rightbottom': 'green', 'righttop': 'orange'}
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.scatter(data['x'], data['y'], c=data['quadrant'].apply(lambda x: colors[x]))
    ax.axhline(y=0, color='black', linestyle='--')
    ax.axvline(x=0, color='black', linestyle='--')
    ax.legend(title='Quadrant', loc='upper right', labels=['Left Bottom', 'Left Top', 'Right Bottom', 'Right Top'])
    plt.title('What is the distribution of points across quadrants?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
